{
  "stem": "10710.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I could count on the fingers, maybe five or six family families which were really considered rich people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The rest of the people were middle class, and a lot of them were very poor.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were families that we have to support them with money.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Which I remember as a boy, I used to go out with a list every Thursday to each store, and everybody gave $0.25, or [NON-ENGLISH], whatever it is-- a zloty, to support the families.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we divided it later in-- in-- In a certain amount of money.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, in-- in Poland, the-- the relationship wasn't so good, especially in the small towns.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're very big anti-Semites.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember going to cheder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After school, I had to go around another block because there was a [NON-ENGLISH] there who was throwing stones at us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were certain-- there a lot of-- the population-- from the goyish population, was very anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Especially when there was a Jewish-- goyish holiday, like Christmas or Easter, a Jew could not go out to the street.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was afraid to go out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "With the stores, we had to be closed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went to school, there was a public school, We went together with the Christian boys.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when we came the recess, especially in the winter when they were throwing snow-- snowballs at us, and doing all kind of mischief.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You see, here in America, the young boys fight back-- we had-- didn't have that mentality to fight back, to the-- to do something back to them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's why they did-- we were defenseless.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were the majority, and we were just a few boys.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember we had to be in the class when-- when they had to sing the-- the songs for Christmas.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
